he connection between pure philosophy and empirical investigation becomes.The aim of this study is to show that the psychological and anthropological interpretations of Kant's pure philosophy are not convincing and at the same time to illustrate some connections between his critical and anthropological investigations by means of an analysis of the theory of the faculties.Against both a "transcendental psychological" and an "anthropological" reading, the book presents Kant's theory of the faculties as a constitutive part of his critical philosophy and shows that there is a close connection between Kant's pure philosophy and his moral aesthetic.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEthics. 0aPhilosophy of mind. 4aGeist. 4aKritische Philosophie. 4aWissen. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Metaphysics.2bisacsh  aVirtues, knowledge, critical philosophy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Philosophy 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023848808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 2000 - 2014z9783110636949oZDB-23-GPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2014z9783110370393oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831103705530 cprintz978311035002940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311035114940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110351149423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110351149/original  a978-3-11-023848-8  DGBA Backlist Philosophy 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA